  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Evaluation of the USAID/Zambia School Water Supply and Hygiene (WASH) and Quality Education Activity</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">IBTCI is leading a summative performance evaluation for the USAID/Zambia School Water Supply and Hygiene (WASH) and Quality Education Activity, which is implemented in 12 districts in the Northern and Muchinga provinces. This evaluation is focusing on determining whether the School WASH and Quality Education activity has achieved the established program objectives of improved access to water and sanitation services in schools in all 12 districts of Northern and Muchinga Provinces, and promotion of education access, gender equity, girls education, teacher retention and improved health outcomes in Zambian schools. IBTCI is designing an evaluation sample for the data collection exercise that will be a fair representation of the activity scope of 950 schools, which are spread across the 12 districts.</narrative>
  </description>
